Some ways to reduce water waste include: 
1. Taking shorter showers; 
2. Installing low-flow showerheads; 
3. Turning off the tap while brushing teeth; 
4. Replacing old, inefficient toilets with WaterSense-labeled ones; 
5. Planting drought-resistant greenery; 
6. Cleaning up pet messes with a pooper scooper, not the hose; 
7. Washing clothes only when necessary and using cold water settings; 
8. Running full loads in the dishwasher and washing machine; 
9. Replacing lawns with artificial turf or hardscapes; 
10. Installing a rain barrel to collect rainwater for watering plants.

